  "description": "Pi extension for file-based todo storage and management.",
  "readme": "# pi-todo-store\n\nStandalone [Pi](https://pi.dev) extension for file-based todo storage and management.\n\nIt provides:\n\n- **`todo`** \u2014 a tool for list, list-all, get, create, update, append, delete, claim, and release operations.\n- **`/todos`** \u2014 a TUI command for browsing and managing project todos.\n\nTodos are stored as markdown files under `.pi/todos` by default, or the path in `PI_TODO_PATH`.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\n# install into your user pi settings\npi install ~/Documents/pi-todo-store\n\n# or try it for the current run only\npi -e ~/Documents/pi-todo-store\n```\n\nPi provides the host packages (`@earendil-works/pi-ai`, `@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent`, `@earendil-works/pi-tui`, `typebox`) at runtime, so they are declared as peer dependencies and are not bundled.\n\n## Acknowledgement\n\nThis extension acknowledges the todo-extension work of GitHub user **mitsuhiko**:\nhttps://github.com/mitsuhiko/agent-stuff/blob/main/extensions/todos.ts\n\n## Develop\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm run pack:check\n```\n",
